cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.IR 

This paper is about semantic segmentation of high-resolution remote sensing images using deep learning techniques. The paper focuses on the computer vision aspect of the problem, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. The use of attention mechanisms and deep learning models also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. The application of the method to robotics and information retrieval also suggests that it could belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) categories.
